## 2. Pseudobulk validation of the SpaceJam/Cell2Location deconvolution model

### Why
There was no way to check whether the custom Pyro deconvolution model (`models/LocationModelWTAMultiExperimentHierarchicalGeneLevel_Modified.py`) actually recovers known cell-type composition. This adds a pseudobulk validation: build synthetic ROIs with known ground-truth composition from held-out snRNA-seq reference cells, run them through the real model, and compare inferred vs. true proportions.

### Design
Each synthetic ROI is built by: (1) drawing a ground-truth composition from a Dirichlet distribution, (2) sampling cells from a **held-out** split of the reference (never the cells used to derive the signature matrix, so recovery isn't circular) and summing their counts, (3) borrowing a real ROI's negative-probe counts, total depth, and batch identity to give the synthetic ROI realistic technical noise, (4) multinomially resampling to the donor's depth.

### Changes
- **`python/pseudobulk_utils.py`** (new): `split_reference_cells()` (stratified train/holdout split), `sample_dirichlet_compositions()`, `build_synthetic_mixture()`, `generate_synthetic_dataset()`.
- **`python/pseudobulk_validation_utils.py`** (new): `evaluate_recovery()` (per-cell-type Pearson/Spearman/RMSE/MAE), `plot_recovery_scatter()`, `plot_recovery_bias_by_abundance()`.
- **`notebooks/06_pseudobulk_validation.py`** (new): end-to-end orchestration per condition (AD+CAA, Control) — reference split, signature re-derivation from train cells only, gene alignment, synthetic dataset generation, model training, evaluation, and output to `results/pseudobulk_validation/<condition>/`.

### Bug caught during review (fixed before considering this done)
`generate_synthetic_dataset()` initially derived its cell-type list from cells present in the **holdout** split, but the trained signature matrix (and thus the model's output columns) spans cell types from the **train** split. If a small cell type was small enough to be kept entirely in train (per `split_reference_cells`'s `min_holdout_cells` logic), the two lists would have different lengths and crash `extract_posterior_abundance()`. Fixed by requiring the full signature-derived cell-type list to be passed in explicitly.

