## 6. Figures for all new analyses (`R/viz_*.R`, `scripts/run_all_figures.R`)

### Why
This adds a ggplot2 figure layer covering all of them.

### Design principles (from the dataviz guidance)
- **Color assigned by the data's job**: sequential viridis for magnitude, a blue-grey-red **diverging** scale centered at 0 for signed quantities (log2 odds ratios, correlations), Okabe-Ito categorical (fixed order, ≤8) for methods/regions. All three are colorblind-safe by construction.
- **The ~46 cell types are never color-encoded** (no palette survives that many categories) — they always sit on an axis (heatmaps, facets, sorted bars).
- Shared theme + palette helpers live in `R/viz_theme.R`; every figure is saved as both PDF and PNG.

### Changes
- **`R/viz_theme.R`** (new): `okabe_ito_palette()`, `theme_analysis()`, `scale_fill_diverging()`/`scale_color_diverging()`, `scale_fill_magnitude()`, `save_figure()`.
- **`R/viz_spatial_stats.R`** (new): contrast effect-size heatmap (region × cell-type × contrast, significance-starred), per-contrast forest plots with CIs, region-heterogeneity interaction bar, co-occurrence correlation heatmap, and an optional co-occurrence network (guarded by igraph/ggraph).
- **`R/viz_pathway.R`** (new): per-cell-type GSEA dot plot (NES) and ranked-gene volcano.
- **`R/viz_marker_concordance.R`** (new): sorted concordance bar with pass/flag coloring (QC view).
- **`R/viz_robustness.R`** (new): leave-one-Scan-out caterpillar plot (full estimate vs. LOO range, significance-flip flagged).
- **`R/viz_deconvolution.R`** (new): method × method correlation heatmap, per-method agreement distribution boxplot, method × cell-type mean-composition heatmap, per-cell-type agreement heatmap (which cell types drive each method's agreement), cross-method spread per cell type (flags method-sensitive vs. method-robust cell types), per-method distance-from-baseline bar, method clustering dendrogram, and per-cell-type method-vs-baseline scatter grid.
- **`python/pseudobulk_validation_utils.py`**: added `plot_recovery_bar()` (sorted per-cell-type recovery metric), completing the pseudobulk plots on the Python side where the rest of that analysis lives.
- **`scripts/run_all_figures.R`** (new): reads all R-side result CSVs and writes figures under `results/figures/<analysis>/`; each figure is guarded so a missing input skips it with a message rather than aborting.
